  systems, and commercial or non-commercial products
- distribute the Software or modified versions of the Software
- make the Software available as part of a hosted service

3. Mandatory KBeam Compatibility

You may modify, extend, brand, configure, or integrate the Software, but every
copy, fork, hosted deployment, and derivative version that includes or is based
on the KBeam-Compatible Login flow must preserve a working KBeam-Compatible
Login path.

You must not remove, rename, disable, obscure, break, or make non-functional
the KBeam-Compatible Login flow or the Protected Compatibility Identifiers.

You must satisfy the Minimum Compatibility Requirements in every copy, fork,
hosted deployment, modified version, derivative work, redistributed copy,
hosted source release, and substantial continuation that includes or is based
on the KBeam-Compatible Login flow, even if You rename the project, reorganize
the code, change the API surface, change the UI, change the storage layer, or
add other login methods.

You may add other login methods, wallet providers, access policies, user
systems, payment flows, or application-specific authorization layers, provided
that the KBeam-Compatible Login flow remains available and interoperable with
the KBeam wallet application.

If You change implementation details, APIs, routes, deployment topology,
storage, frontend UI, or session handling, You are responsible for ensuring
that KBeam users can still unlock the integrated protected area through the
KBeam-Compatible Login flow.

